Consultant Paediatric Neurologist (Abu Dhabi UAE)
Job Seekers
|
|
what:
where:
Abu Dhabi
This is an excellent opportunity to join a prestigious Government hospital with a strong clinical and academic reputation. The hospital, which is a tertiary care centre, seeks to recruit an outstanding Consultant Paediatric Neurologist who can develop the service. The position attracts a very attractive salary package which is tax free.
Key Performance Criteria:
Develop clinically sound Paediatric Neurology service within JCI clinical governance frameworks Educate and supervise medical students, residents and Specialists in Paediatrics
Essential Qualifications and Experience *Residency or other recognised structured postgraduate training programme in Paediatrics and subspeciality training in Neurology in North America or Western country
Appropriate Board Certification or Fellowship for the HAAD Consultant License (see below and attached document). Qualifications listed as Tier 1 only are accepted. Minimum 2 years experience as a Consultant or Attending physician after Board Certification or Specialist Registration. Excellent spoken and written English Knowledge of Arabic desirable
To apply, please send a detailed CV with full employment history and a description of scope of practice.
